WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.892 --> 00:00:02.685
<i>Previously on</i>
Designated Survivor...

2
00:00:02.769 --> 00:00:04.645
I've been posted full-time
with the British embassy.

3
00:00:04.729 --> 00:00:06.564
Effective immediately.

4
00:00:09.275 --> 00:00:11.319
Did you take a vacation on St. Lucia?

5
00:00:11.402 --> 00:00:15.323
Every year. my daughter and I
take one trip together.

6
00:00:15.406 --> 00:00:16.866
This year. St. Lucia.

7
00:00:16.949 --> 00:00:19.660
You're being subpoenaed by Foerstel?
For what?

8
00:00:19.744 --> 00:00:23.372
He's found a St. Lucian bank account
set up by Eric Little.

9
00:00:23.456 --> 00:00:26.375
six months ago. in my name.

10
00:00:26.459 --> 00:00:27.502
I'm being set up.

11
00:00:27.585 --> 00:00:29.253
Where are we
with Little's murder investigation?

12
00:00:29.337 --> 00:00:30.964
<i>Nothing on that front. sir.</i>

13
00:00:31.047 --> 00:00:33.257
Were you able to tie Little to Lloyd?

14
00:00:33.341 --> 00:00:35.343
There's no evidence that connects them.

15
00:00:35.426 --> 00:00:37.053
You're the greatest thing
since sliced bread.

16
00:00:37.136 --> 00:00:38.805
And bread is great.

17
00:00:38.888 --> 00:00:42.141
Fundamentally great. Like water.
Or air. Or you.

18
00:00:44.268 --> 00:00:45.603
Is there a problem?

19
00:00:45.686 --> 00:00:47.146
Step out of the vehicle.

20
00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:48.439
The charges were dismissed.

21
00:00:48.523 --> 00:00:50.775
But my duty to inform
the president wasn't.

22
00:01:21.889 --> 00:01:23.057
Three-letter day?

23
00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:25.726
Every month.
the White House receives 10.000 letters.

24
00:01:25.810 --> 00:01:27.687
The president chooses three letters
to answer.

25
00:01:27.770 --> 00:01:28.896
How does that involve us?

26
00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:31.524
We investigate the requests
and advise the president.

27
00:01:31.607 --> 00:01:32.733
- That's exciting.
- Yeah.

28
00:01:32.817 --> 00:01:34.068
Three-letter day can be a red-letter day.

29
00:01:34.151 --> 00:01:35.945
- I'm not doing this.
- For some.

30
00:01:36.028 --> 00:01:38.614
I don't like letters.
I don't read or write them.

31
00:01:38.698 --> 00:01:41.325
- Whose asinine idea was this?
- The president's.

32
00:01:41.409 --> 00:01:42.910
- I'm in.
- Attaboy.

33
00:01:42.994 --> 00:01:45.538
- Three-letter day. <i>amigo.</i>
- Oh. somebody please shoot me.

34
00:01:45.621 --> 00:01:46.998
- Hey.
- Hi.

35
00:01:48.583 --> 00:01:50.918
Today is not just simply symbolic.

36
00:01:51.002 --> 00:01:53.796
Today. we are gonna
truly serve the electorate

37
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:56.674
by trying to answer
their specific requests.

38
00:01:57.383 --> 00:01:59.010
Aaron and Emily.

39
00:01:59.093 --> 00:02:01.971
this was written by the widow
of Daniel Goff. Sergeant First Class.

40
00:02:02.054 --> 00:02:04.557
She asks why her husband
was denied the Medal of Honor

41
00:02:04.640 --> 00:02:08.186
for his ultimate sacrifice and bravery
during Operation Enduring Freedom.

42
00:02:08.269 --> 00:02:09.312
- On it.
- Absolutely.

43
00:02:09.395 --> 00:02:10.688
Thank you.

44
00:02:10.771 --> 00:02:12.064
Seth and Lyor.

45
00:02:12.148 --> 00:02:15.776
help Mr. Adamson figure out
what's killing his bees.

46
00:02:15.860 --> 00:02:17.820
- Bees?
- Yes. bees.

47
00:02:17.904 --> 00:02:19.906
They are an indicator species.

48
00:02:19.989 --> 00:02:22.325
They pollinate over 80% of our crops.

49
00:02:22.408 --> 00:02:25.119
They die. plants die.
man will shortly follow.

50
00:02:25.203 --> 00:02:29.624
It's in our interest to do what we can
to find out what's killing his bees.

51
00:02:29.707 --> 00:02:33.336
- Thank you. This is a solemn honor.
- I'm sure you'll do great.

52
00:02:35.838 --> 00:02:37.465
- Jackpot!
- Snake eyes.

53
00:02:37.548 --> 00:02:41.802
Kendra. this is a request for a pardon
in a federal death penalty case.

54
00:02:41.886 --> 00:02:45.139
There hasn't been a federal execution
since 2003.

55
00:02:45.222 --> 00:02:48.434
He's scheduled to die by lethal injection
this Friday.

56
00:02:48.517 --> 00:02:51.395
An anonymous letter
from Winter Haven. Florida.

57
00:02:51.479 --> 00:02:53.648
Seeking clemency for Chandler Dern?

58
00:02:53.731 --> 00:02:58.611
He was a pharmacist convicted of killing
a DEA agent in 2001.

59
00:02:58.694 --> 00:03:03.699
This writer says that Dern appealed
his sentence. but not his conviction.

60
00:03:03.783 --> 00:03:06.577
That's what caught my eye.
Strange. right?

61
00:03:06.661 --> 00:03:08.329
Unheard of. given the stakes.

62
00:03:08.412 --> 00:03:10.790
I'm not inclined to impose my judgment
over a jury's.

63
00:03:10.873 --> 00:03:13.501
But if you found anything
to indicate manifest injustice.

64
00:03:13.584 --> 00:03:15.836
- I would wanna know.
- I'll get cracking.

65
00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:17.296
You got 72 hours.

66
00:03:17.380 --> 00:03:19.799
Understood. Sir. we have another issue.

67
00:03:19.882 --> 00:03:23.594
There's been a development in regards
to your wife's subpoena. We should talk.

68
00:03:24.595 --> 00:03:26.847
Foerstel's offering
to seal the proceedings?

69
00:03:26.931 --> 00:03:28.057
With one condition.

70
00:03:28.140 --> 00:03:29.892
That you don't move
to quash your subpoena.

71
00:03:29.976 --> 00:03:33.271
So an inducement.
Secrecy in exchange for cooperation.

72
00:03:33.354 --> 00:03:37.149
If Alex appears and her answers lead
to an indictment. that will go public.

73
00:03:37.233 --> 00:03:38.567
It's a calculated risk.

74
00:03:38.651 --> 00:03:40.695
What are the odds
that you can get this tossed?

75
00:03:40.778 --> 00:03:42.029
It's a coin flip.

76
00:03:42.113 --> 00:03:45.241
The case against you
is wildly circumstantial.

77
00:03:45.324 --> 00:03:48.953
With one exception. The account
in St. Lucia in your name

78
00:03:49.036 --> 00:03:50.705
that Eric Little opened is damning.

79
00:03:50.788 --> 00:03:53.082
Unless Hannah Wells can find
the banker who set it up.

80
00:03:53.165 --> 00:03:54.834
we cannot clear you.

81
00:03:59.672 --> 00:04:01.424
Only the banker can prove

82
00:04:01.507 --> 00:04:04.135
that the First Lady's St. Lucia account
is a Lloyd set-up.

83
00:04:04.218 --> 00:04:06.303
- They'll never give you his name.
- <i>We'll see.</i>

84
00:04:06.387 --> 00:04:08.097
I can be very persuasive.

85
00:04:09.181 --> 00:04:12.351
Hello. I'm Ms. Sloane.
I'm here to see Mr. Brewer.

86
00:04:12.435 --> 00:04:14.395
You'd like to open an account
in St. Lucia?

87
00:04:14.478 --> 00:04:15.313
Yes.

88
00:04:15.396 --> 00:04:17.148
- On someone's behalf?
- Yes.

89
00:04:17.231 --> 00:04:19.900
That is a third-party service
we do not offer.

90
00:04:19.984 --> 00:04:22.069
I have it from a trusted friend

91
00:04:22.153 --> 00:04:24.989
that one of your officers
does offer the service.

92
00:04:25.072 --> 00:04:25.948
Is that so?

93
00:04:26.032 --> 00:04:28.034
If you could put me in touch
with the right person.

94
00:04:28.117 --> 00:04:29.577
I'd be happy to pay a premium.

95
00:04:29.660 --> 00:04:31.203
Sorry. but we are unable to help you.

96
00:04:31.287 --> 00:04:32.955
If you could give me the name
of the officer...

97
00:04:33.039 --> 00:04:35.082
That will be all. Have a good day.

98
00:04:56.103 --> 00:04:58.230
Don't play with guns
if you don't know how to use them.

99
00:04:58.314 --> 00:05:00.441
Me. I know how to use them.

100
00:05:00.524 --> 00:05:03.152
Would you like to give me the name
of that bank officer?

101
00:05:05.196 --> 00:05:07.198
Quashing this will come down to the judge.

102
00:05:07.281 --> 00:05:09.992
Yes. And the optics of giving
the First Lady a pass

103
00:05:10.076 --> 00:05:11.118
could weigh heavily on them.

104
00:05:11.202 --> 00:05:13.913
What should weigh heavily on them
is that this is a set-up.

105
00:05:13.996 --> 00:05:15.998
- Alex.
- We're moving to quash. Tom.

106
00:05:18.918 --> 00:05:20.961
Could you give us a moment?
We need to discuss this.

107
00:05:21.045 --> 00:05:23.089
- Yes. sir.
- Thank you.

108
00:05:25.007 --> 00:05:28.594
- This witch hunt has lasted months.
- I know.

109
00:05:28.677 --> 00:05:30.554
I don't want to give Foerstel
any more oxygen.

110
00:05:30.638 --> 00:05:34.391
Every procedural maneuver. stratagem.
we'll avail ourselves of all of it.

111
00:05:34.475 --> 00:05:36.435
That's only putting off the inevitable.

112
00:05:36.519 --> 00:05:37.436
Foerstel won't back down

113
00:05:37.520 --> 00:05:39.439
because you quote
the <i>Federal Rules of Procedure.</i>

114
00:05:39.522 --> 00:05:43.400
- It's our only viable tactic.
- It's what we've been doing so far.

115
00:05:43.484 --> 00:05:45.194
Playing defense.
and look where it's gotten us.

116
00:05:45.277 --> 00:05:48.239
- Closer to the precipice.
- Then let's step back.

117
00:05:48.322 --> 00:05:50.658
Alex. you are a fighter.

118
00:05:51.575 --> 00:05:53.911
It's one of the many things
I love about you.

119
00:05:53.994 --> 00:05:55.788
But we're not fighting this. we're hiding.

120
00:05:55.871 --> 00:05:58.082
Pretending like it'll blow over.
It won't.

121
00:05:58.165 --> 00:06:00.584
This storm has been coming at us
for a while.

122
00:06:00.668 --> 00:06:02.086
We tried to outrun it. but we couldn't.

123
00:06:02.169 --> 00:06:05.714
So we take a different tact. we dig in.
We fight this thing.

124
00:06:12.281 --> 00:06:17.281
Subtitles by explosiveskull

125
00:06:18.153 --> 00:06:20.655
I roll over this morning
and you're not there.

126
00:06:20.739 --> 00:06:23.825
- That can give a guy a complex.
- You needed your beauty sleep.

127
00:06:23.909 --> 00:06:25.786
I could've helped you
track down the banker

128
00:06:25.869 --> 00:06:27.329
who helped frame the First Lady.

129
00:06:27.412 --> 00:06:29.623
It wasn't a two-man job.

130
00:06:29.706 --> 00:06:32.250
You. Hannah Wells. are a lone wolf.

131
00:06:32.334 --> 00:06:34.711
Who hunted down the banker's name.

132
00:06:34.795 --> 00:06:35.879
Touché.

133
00:06:36.755 --> 00:06:39.091
Anything on our rogue banker?

134
00:06:39.174 --> 00:06:44.179
TSA confirms Alfonso Lang flew
from Hewanorra to Dulles four days ago.

135
00:06:44.262 --> 00:06:45.180
Did he have a sheet?

136
00:06:45.263 --> 00:06:46.515
A lot of raps for money laundering.

137
00:06:46.598 --> 00:06:48.934
all of which he's beaten.
otherwise he'd be on the no-fly list.

138
00:06:49.017 --> 00:06:50.393
You got a 411 on his location?

139
00:06:50.477 --> 00:06:53.230
Just a contact at Interpol
telling me he meets with clients

140
00:06:53.313 --> 00:06:55.690
in the district regularly
to set up tax scams.

141
00:06:55.774 --> 00:06:57.275
I'll contact the embassy.

142
00:06:57.359 --> 00:06:59.903
See if he's on one of their watch lists
and tripped a wire.

143
00:06:59.986 --> 00:07:01.196
St. Lucia's a British protectorate.

144
00:07:01.279 --> 00:07:03.949
Actually. St. Lucia's a sovereign nation.
Part of the Commonwealth.

145
00:07:04.032 --> 00:07:06.284
Well done. Charles.
You should go on <i>Jeopardy!</i>

146
00:07:06.368 --> 00:07:07.452
And you should...

147
00:07:08.495 --> 00:07:10.163
Go on it. too.

148
00:07:11.540 --> 00:07:13.125
Hey. Kendra.

149
00:07:14.376 --> 00:07:16.461
Of course. I'll be right there.

150
00:07:17.337 --> 00:07:19.589
White House Counsel needs help
with an urgent matter.

151
00:07:19.673 --> 00:07:21.716
No problem.
I'll call you as soon as I find anything.

152
00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:24.803
All right. Play nice. boys.

153
00:07:34.563 --> 00:07:36.231
No. I don't know who sent it.

154
00:07:36.982 --> 00:07:38.775
But every word's true.
I'm innocent.

155
00:07:38.859 --> 00:07:40.485
We reviewed your file.

156
00:07:40.569 --> 00:07:44.698
You were convicted of murdering
a DEA agent named Carl Marley in 2001.

157
00:07:44.781 --> 00:07:46.491
A ketamine sting gone bad.

158
00:07:46.575 --> 00:07:48.118
The prosecutor convinced the jury

159
00:07:48.201 --> 00:07:49.995
that your pharmacy
was in financial trouble.

160
00:07:50.078 --> 00:07:52.247
And that I was selling ketamine
on the black market

161
00:07:52.330 --> 00:07:53.665
when I'd never even jaywalked?

162
00:07:53.748 --> 00:07:56.251
His body was found in a park
near your store.

163
00:07:56.334 --> 00:07:58.462
Shot in the face with a gun
that was never located.

164
00:07:58.545 --> 00:08:01.465
Traces of his blood were found
on your storage room floor.

165
00:08:01.548 --> 00:08:04.885
Twenty people were in that room every day.
Anyone could've tracked it in.

166
00:08:04.968 --> 00:08:07.596
What about your trial lawyer?
Can we talk to him?

167
00:08:07.679 --> 00:08:10.765
No. He died three years ago.

168
00:08:10.849 --> 00:08:12.684
But he was pretty worthless
when he was alive.

169
00:08:12.767 --> 00:08:15.479
How much money did you have left
after the trial?

170
00:08:16.313 --> 00:08:20.525
As it turned out.
just enough to appeal the sentence.

171
00:08:20.609 --> 00:08:25.071
Mr. Dern.
this was a highly circumstantial case.

172
00:08:25.822 --> 00:08:30.368
Your lawyer did a bad job.
We're going to look into this for you.

173
00:08:30.452 --> 00:08:34.956
That's great.
But I believe I've exhausted my appeals.

174
00:08:35.040 --> 00:08:37.751
It wouldn't be an appeal.
It would be a commutation.

175
00:08:37.834 --> 00:08:40.587
If the president were to grant that.
I wouldn't have words.

176
00:08:40.670 --> 00:08:43.632
But I've been waiting for justice
a long time. and it's never come.

177
00:08:44.758 --> 00:08:46.218
Hope is a dangerous thing.

178
00:08:47.344 --> 00:08:50.889
I don't wanna die a coward praying
for a reprieve that's never coming.

179
00:08:51.723 --> 00:08:53.892
That's not a legacy
I want for my children.

180
00:08:54.518 --> 00:08:56.770
Then don't pray. Prepare.

181
00:08:56.853 --> 00:08:58.730
And let us do our thing.

182
00:08:58.813 --> 00:09:01.149
Chandler Dern has two master's degrees.

183
00:09:01.233 --> 00:09:04.861
Does it make sense to you
that a lawyer. even a crooked one.

184
00:09:04.945 --> 00:09:07.739
could convince him that
it was a good idea not to appeal?

185
00:09:07.822 --> 00:09:09.157
Not even a little bit.

186
00:09:09.241 --> 00:09:12.869
He has a son in Gaithersburg.
Let's see what he has to say.

187
00:09:12.953 --> 00:09:14.788
Thanks for talking to us.

188
00:09:14.871 --> 00:09:16.831
I'm thrilled that you're looking
into my father's sentence.

189
00:09:16.915 --> 00:09:19.334
Is there a chance
the president might step in?

190
00:09:19.417 --> 00:09:21.086
It depends on our investigation.

191
00:09:21.670 --> 00:09:22.712
How can I help?

192
00:09:22.796 --> 00:09:25.507
Is there a reason your father
wouldn't be forthcoming with us?

193
00:09:26.132 --> 00:09:28.385
- What did he tell you?
- It's not what he told us.

194
00:09:28.468 --> 00:09:30.136
It's what we're asking you to tell us.

195
00:09:30.220 --> 00:09:33.098
It's interesting.
You're devoted to your father.

196
00:09:33.181 --> 00:09:36.184
Visitor logs at the prison say
you're there twice a week.

197
00:09:36.268 --> 00:09:39.563
But your younger sister. Tracy.
hasn't been to see him in 16 years.

198
00:09:39.646 --> 00:09:40.981
We're wondering why.

199
00:09:43.066 --> 00:09:44.776
My mom died when I was six.

200
00:09:45.944 --> 00:09:48.572
I was 17 when they took him away. and...

201
00:09:49.406 --> 00:09:50.448
I got through it.

202
00:09:50.532 --> 00:09:52.576
I set up an auto repair business.

203
00:09:52.659 --> 00:09:58.123
- Tracy. she wasn't so lucky.
- But my dad. he...

204
00:09:58.206 --> 00:10:01.543
He told us to always put family first.
I'm not talking about Tracy.

205
00:10:01.626 --> 00:10:04.296
We don't have time for games.
Your father's life is on the line.

206
00:10:06.548 --> 00:10:10.594
My sister. she's always had problems
with drugs.

207
00:10:10.677 --> 00:10:13.138
She used to hang out
with some bad people.

208
00:10:13.221 --> 00:10:17.517
I think that my father was afraid
his investigation would implicate her.

209
00:10:17.601 --> 00:10:20.312
Were those people used as a defense
in your father's trial?

210
00:10:20.395 --> 00:10:21.438
My dad wouldn't allow that.

211
00:10:21.521 --> 00:10:23.440
- Where can we find your sister?
- No.

212
00:10:23.523 --> 00:10:25.859
If he knew I told you any of this.
he would disown me.

213
00:10:25.942 --> 00:10:28.653
Frank. your father is about to be
put to death.

214
00:10:28.737 --> 00:10:30.947
I don't think disowning you
is the issue here.

215
00:10:35.327 --> 00:10:37.120
Your husband was
very handsome. Mrs. Goff.

216
00:10:37.203 --> 00:10:38.997
Thank you.

217
00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:40.624
Daniel was my everything.

218
00:10:41.166 --> 00:10:44.377
The president was moved by your letter.
Could you tell us more?

219
00:10:45.337 --> 00:10:49.007
Daniel was sent to Kandahar
in 2013 to battle ISIL.

220
00:10:49.674 --> 00:10:51.593
Part of the international
peacekeeping force.

221
00:10:51.676 --> 00:10:55.013
Yes. One of the first American casualties.

222
00:10:55.764 --> 00:10:59.809
At his funeral. one of his soldiers.
Corporal Mankiewicz. told me

223
00:10:59.893 --> 00:11:04.481
Daniel single-handedly kept the insurgents
at bay until help could arrive.

224
00:11:04.564 --> 00:11:07.442
He stopped them from overrunning
the American position.

225
00:11:07.525 --> 00:11:11.112
- That sounds like conspicuous bravery.
- I think so.

226
00:11:11.196 --> 00:11:14.115
But I wrote his CO. Colonel Baines...

227
00:11:15.158 --> 00:11:16.743
And he ignored me.

228
00:11:18.870 --> 00:11:19.954
Uh...

229
00:11:20.955 --> 00:11:25.710
Twelve letters over the past four years.
and he didn't answer one.

230
00:11:25.794 --> 00:11:29.130
Daniel once told me
Special Forces was like family.

231
00:11:29.214 --> 00:11:31.549
but this is not how you treat family.

232
00:11:34.052 --> 00:11:37.222
Our son. Danny Junior. is seven now.

233
00:11:38.390 --> 00:11:40.100
Asking about his father.

234
00:11:41.684 --> 00:11:44.354
I would like to tell him
his dad was a war hero.

235
00:11:44.437 --> 00:11:47.482
not just some stranger
who died 10.000 miles away.

236
00:11:51.111 --> 00:11:54.072
On behalf of the president.
we promise to look into this.

237
00:11:55.073 --> 00:11:56.074
Thank you.

238
00:12:00.745 --> 00:12:03.623
Sergeant Goff's unit was ambushed
in Kandahar.

239
00:12:03.706 --> 00:12:07.085
Mortars. RPGs. Machine guns.
They were pinned down for hours.

240
00:12:07.168 --> 00:12:08.753
Took a lot of casualties.

241
00:12:08.837 --> 00:12:11.172
You deserve a medal
for even coming through that.

242
00:12:11.256 --> 00:12:13.174
I agree. But Goff wasn't there.

243
00:12:13.967 --> 00:12:15.343
Where was he?

244
00:12:15.427 --> 00:12:17.137
He was doing recon
in the Kabul Dwarza district.

245
00:12:17.220 --> 00:12:19.431
It's a click away.
that's where the IED took him out.

246
00:12:19.514 --> 00:12:21.641
Did you explain this
to Sergeant Goff's widow?

247
00:12:21.724 --> 00:12:24.102
Repeatedly. But she kept writing.

248
00:12:24.185 --> 00:12:26.604
She is not the first widow
that wants recognition for her husband.

249
00:12:26.688 --> 00:12:27.939
but facts are facts.

250
00:12:28.022 --> 00:12:30.233
After some time. I had to stop responding.

251
00:12:30.316 --> 00:12:33.319
- Were there any other witnesses?
- Just Corporal Mankiewicz.

252
00:12:33.403 --> 00:12:35.822
He put the idea of a medal in her ear.

253
00:12:39.451 --> 00:12:42.120
- So where's Mankiewicz now?
- He's dead. sir.

254
00:12:42.203 --> 00:12:44.080
He committed suicide
a year after leaving the service.

255
00:12:44.164 --> 00:12:47.000
According to this.
he was the only potential witness left.

256
00:12:47.459 --> 00:12:48.835
I guess that's that.

257
00:12:50.128 --> 00:12:53.298
- Mike. you wanna add something?
- It's not appropriate. sir.

258
00:12:53.381 --> 00:12:55.592
- It is if I'm asking.
- It's just...

259
00:12:55.675 --> 00:12:57.135
That was Goff's unit.

260
00:12:57.218 --> 00:12:59.512
It doesn't make sense
he'd be a click away from his men

261
00:12:59.596 --> 00:13:01.973
if they were expecting hostiles.
which they would've been.

262
00:13:02.056 --> 00:13:03.975
You think Colonel Baines is mistaken.

263
00:13:04.058 --> 00:13:06.436
In my opinion. sir.

264
00:13:08.229 --> 00:13:10.523
Mike served six years. Special Forces.

265
00:13:10.607 --> 00:13:13.735
If he doesn't think something's adding up.
something's not adding up.

266
00:13:13.818 --> 00:13:15.111
- Dig deeper.
- Yes. sir.

267
00:13:15.195 --> 00:13:16.988
- Emily. can I borrow you?
- Of course. sir.

268
00:13:17.071 --> 00:13:19.741
They've been banging the drum on this
all week.

269
00:13:19.824 --> 00:13:20.867
The media's picked it up.

270
00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:23.369
That's why Foerstel's trying to induce
Alex to testify now.

271
00:13:23.453 --> 00:13:24.621
He knows the heat's turning up.

272
00:13:24.704 --> 00:13:26.498
He's trying to take advantage
of the timing.

273
00:13:26.581 --> 00:13:28.374
I got a message from his office today.

274
00:13:28.458 --> 00:13:32.045
He has an update on the Cincinnati area
police abuse investigation.

275
00:13:32.128 --> 00:13:33.546
Why? That's been dormant for months.

276
00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:36.007
- The timing's odd.
- No. it's not.

277
00:13:36.466 --> 00:13:38.718
He wants to talk off the record
about my wife's subpoena.

278
00:13:38.801 --> 00:13:40.929
That's why he contacted you
instead of Kendra.

279
00:13:41.012 --> 00:13:43.556
- Do you want me to take the meeting?
- Yes.

280
00:13:43.640 --> 00:13:45.892
The second he talks about Icarus.
walk away.

281
00:13:45.975 --> 00:13:48.436
I don't want this office
to have the slightest appearance

282
00:13:48.520 --> 00:13:50.146
of trying to obstruct this investigation.

283
00:13:50.230 --> 00:13:52.774
- Understood.
- Thank you.

284
00:13:57.278 --> 00:13:59.656
- Mr. Director.
- Thanks for meeting me.

285
00:13:59.739 --> 00:14:02.242
You have an update
on the Cincinnati investigation?

286
00:14:02.325 --> 00:14:06.871
Yes. My considered opinion is
there may have been wrongdoing.

287
00:14:07.664 --> 00:14:09.290
Serious wrongdoing.

288
00:14:09.374 --> 00:14:14.087
And our opinion is that the facts to date
don't remotely support that conclusion.

289
00:14:14.170 --> 00:14:17.090
It's provisional opinion. which is why
an investigation has to continue.

290
00:14:17.173 --> 00:14:18.216
Despite the fact you're chasing

291
00:14:18.299 --> 00:14:20.760
what any objective observer
would describe as innuendo.

292
00:14:20.844 --> 00:14:22.136
Wild conspiracy theories.

293
00:14:22.220 --> 00:14:25.181
All investigations chase those things
until they disclose the truth.

294
00:14:25.265 --> 00:14:26.307
Or turn up nothing.

295
00:14:26.391 --> 00:14:29.853
Meanwhile. damage is done
to those you're investigating.

296
00:14:29.936 --> 00:14:33.106
If the subjects of this investigation
are innocent. there won't be any damage.

297
00:14:33.189 --> 00:14:35.817
We both know that's not true.

298
00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:39.404
Reputations can be harmed.
Institutions eroded.

299
00:14:39.487 --> 00:14:41.281
That's not my concern.

300
00:14:41.364 --> 00:14:43.741
Is that what you want me
to tell the president?

301
00:14:45.952 --> 00:14:49.998
Tell him Cincinnati is not personal.
It's professional.

302
00:14:50.081 --> 00:14:53.376
And I owe a duty to the American people
to follow this to the end of the line.

303
00:14:54.168 --> 00:14:55.628
No matter what.

304
00:15:02.129 --> 00:15:04.881
Foerstel wanted to underscore
he wouldn't stand down.

305
00:15:04.965 --> 00:15:07.342
- Didn't think he would.
- And here's why.

306
00:15:07.426 --> 00:15:09.553
The media's covering
the Icarus investigation.

307
00:15:09.636 --> 00:15:12.931
He's staking his professional credibility
on the outcome.

308
00:15:13.014 --> 00:15:14.599
Not a problem
if you're a career civil servant.

309
00:15:14.683 --> 00:15:15.726
Which he is.

310
00:15:15.809 --> 00:15:18.311
Not for long.
I played a hunch. sir.

311
00:15:18.395 --> 00:15:21.148
I reached out to a source in Albany.
where he's from. and it turns out.

312
00:15:21.231 --> 00:15:24.776
he formed an exploratory committee
for a 2018 New York Senate run.

313
00:15:24.860 --> 00:15:26.611
right when the Icarus investigation began.

314
00:15:26.695 --> 00:15:29.072
He has a secret PAC in the works. too.

315
00:15:29.156 --> 00:15:30.699
They've already raised
half a million dollars.

316
00:15:30.782 --> 00:15:32.367
He's doing it on the back
of the investigation.

317
00:15:32.451 --> 00:15:34.369
We know you respect process.

318
00:15:34.453 --> 00:15:37.831
so we're recommending you appoint
a special prosecutor to investigate.

319
00:15:37.914 --> 00:15:40.208
- A special prosecutor?
- Yes. sir.

320
00:15:40.292 --> 00:15:41.543
It doesn't end the Icarus investigation.

321
00:15:41.626 --> 00:15:43.378
It simply removes Foerstel
from the equation.

322
00:15:43.462 --> 00:15:45.589
Which is in the best interest
of the White House

323
00:15:45.672 --> 00:15:47.007
since he may have ulterior motives.

324
00:15:47.090 --> 00:15:49.259
Ambition is not an ulterior motive.

325
00:15:49.342 --> 00:15:51.595
It's a by-product of the work
that gets done in this town

326
00:15:51.678 --> 00:15:52.721
and no one's immune.

327
00:15:52.804 --> 00:15:54.556
- Present company included.
- Sir...

328
00:15:54.639 --> 00:15:56.808
With regards to a special prosecutor.

329
00:15:56.892 --> 00:15:59.269
history tells me
that they're runaway trains.

330
00:15:59.352 --> 00:16:02.230
One investigation turns into another.
etcetera.

331
00:16:02.314 --> 00:16:03.190
Way too risky.

332
00:16:03.273 --> 00:16:05.942
It's the lesser of two evils.
A risk we can manage.

333
00:16:06.026 --> 00:16:07.277
Emily. I get it.

334
00:16:08.111 --> 00:16:09.988
I'll take it under advisement. Thank you.

335
00:16:10.071 --> 00:16:12.032
Thank you. Mr. President.

336
00:16:23.001 --> 00:16:25.420
Hey. so three-letter day. huh?

337
00:16:25.504 --> 00:16:26.588
Yeah. Three-letter day.

338
00:16:26.671 --> 00:16:29.090
Wait. hang on. Um. can I talk to you?

339
00:16:29.174 --> 00:16:30.467
Uh. I've got a thing I...

340
00:16:30.550 --> 00:16:32.761
Look. um. I have a thing. too. okay?

341
00:16:32.844 --> 00:16:34.054
It's called walking on eggshells.

342
00:16:34.137 --> 00:16:36.973
which is what I feel like I've been doing
the last few days.

343
00:16:37.057 --> 00:16:39.684
I'm wondering if you told
the president that I got arrested

344
00:16:39.768 --> 00:16:42.479
for covering up my brother's drugs.
and what that means for me.

345
00:16:42.562 --> 00:16:46.233
Because I'm also obsessed
with this thing called job security.

346
00:16:46.316 --> 00:16:48.276
It's an evolving situation.

347
00:16:49.277 --> 00:16:50.403
"Evolving." Got it.

348
00:16:51.571 --> 00:16:52.405
Yeah.

349
00:16:52.489 --> 00:16:54.157
That's also a thing.

350
00:16:54.241 --> 00:16:55.283
Oh.

351
00:16:58.703 --> 00:17:01.206
Interesting fact.
A colony rears several queens at once.

352
00:17:01.289 --> 00:17:05.001
The first queen that hatches
stings the others to death in their cells.

353
00:17:05.085 --> 00:17:08.797
If two emerge at once.
they fight until one is killed.

354
00:17:08.880 --> 00:17:10.298
It's like an election.

355
00:17:14.553 --> 00:17:16.972
I didn't set out to be an apiarist.

356
00:17:17.055 --> 00:17:20.684
It began as a hobby. and before I knew it.
I had three colonies.

357
00:17:20.767 --> 00:17:22.352
Their upkeep must take a lot of time.

358
00:17:22.435 --> 00:17:26.898
Yes. But I now harvest $4.000 a month
worth of honey from my hives.

359
00:17:26.982 --> 00:17:28.817
That's excellent. So. how can we help?

360
00:17:28.900 --> 00:17:31.194
Eddie thinks the FAA is killing our bees.

361
00:17:31.278 --> 00:17:33.738
Really? How?

362
00:17:33.822 --> 00:17:37.158
That new Air Route
Surveillance Radar facility.

363
00:17:37.242 --> 00:17:39.744
it opened around the time of the die-off.

364
00:17:39.828 --> 00:17:42.789
Bees navigate using magnetic fields.

365
00:17:42.873 --> 00:17:44.833
I think the radar is disrupting that.

366
00:17:44.916 --> 00:17:46.751
Are they flying into trees?

367
00:17:46.835 --> 00:17:49.421
No. Seth.
They're insects. not imbeciles.

368
00:17:49.504 --> 00:17:51.506
They use a solar compass to navigate.

369
00:17:51.590 --> 00:17:54.509
Disrupt that.
you compromise their spatial memory.

370
00:17:54.593 --> 00:17:57.012
They can't find their food.

371
00:17:57.095 --> 00:17:59.139
You must be a fellow melittologist.

372
00:17:59.222 --> 00:18:02.183
I dabble. So you've spoken with the ARSR?

373
00:18:02.267 --> 00:18:06.438
Yes. I told them two of my three
colonies had been completely wiped out.

374
00:18:06.521 --> 00:18:10.275
But they ignored me.
That's why I wrote the president a letter.

375
00:18:10.358 --> 00:18:13.153
- Eddie's very proactive.
- So is the White House.

376
00:18:13.236 --> 00:18:15.280
Oh. we didn't mean
to put you to all this trouble.

377
00:18:15.363 --> 00:18:17.240
Oh. no. The trouble will be the FAA's.

378
00:18:17.324 --> 00:18:19.701
Tell <i>Apis cerana</i> to stand by.
Help's on the way.

379
00:18:21.077 --> 00:18:23.788
Uh. we'll be in touch.

380
00:18:28.668 --> 00:18:29.711
Interesting fact.

381
00:18:29.794 --> 00:18:32.130
- Bees never sleep.
- I don't care.

382
00:18:32.213 --> 00:18:34.716
They're the only insect
that produces food for humans.

383
00:18:34.799 --> 00:18:36.009
I still don't care.

384
00:18:36.092 --> 00:18:38.595
Oh. you've been stung. haven't you?

385
00:18:38.678 --> 00:18:39.679
Hey. Ms. Slater.

386
00:18:39.763 --> 00:18:42.682
Seth Wright. This is Lyor Boone.
Thank you so much for coming.

387
00:18:42.766 --> 00:18:46.353
On behalf of the FAA. we're thrilled
the president has an interest in aviation.

388
00:18:46.436 --> 00:18:48.355
Oh. he doesn't.
His interest is in bees.

389
00:18:48.438 --> 00:18:52.525
- Oh. God. Not that Eddie guy again.
- You remember him?

390
00:18:52.609 --> 00:18:56.154
As the administrator of the ARSR.
I have a hard time forgetting someone

391
00:18:56.237 --> 00:18:58.865
I nearly got a restraining order against.

392
00:18:58.949 --> 00:19:02.118
- The letters. The calls. The pickets.
- All of which you ignored.

393
00:19:02.202 --> 00:19:03.536
No. we didn't.

394
00:19:03.620 --> 00:19:08.333
We tried to reach an amicable settlement.
but the problem resolved itself.

395
00:19:08.416 --> 00:19:09.793
Or I thought it did.

396
00:19:09.876 --> 00:19:12.003
- Who told you that?
- Helen Adamson.

397
00:19:14.756 --> 00:19:15.632
His wife?

398
00:19:19.970 --> 00:19:21.554
That's her. Chandler's daughter.

399
00:19:21.638 --> 00:19:26.017
Ms. Dern? I'm Hannah Wells. FBI.

400
00:19:26.101 --> 00:19:28.019
This is Kendra Daynes.
The White House Counsel.

401
00:19:28.103 --> 00:19:30.313
- I've left you messages.
- I've nothing to say.

402
00:19:30.397 --> 00:19:33.692
It's about your dad.
You remember him. don't you?

403
00:19:34.609 --> 00:19:36.111
Winter Haven?
You spend a lot of time there?

404
00:19:36.194 --> 00:19:37.654
Please leave me alone.

405
00:19:37.737 --> 00:19:39.739
- Did you write to us about your Dad?
- No.

406
00:19:40.615 --> 00:19:44.369
We work for the White House.
If your Dad is innocent. we can save him.

407
00:19:44.452 --> 00:19:45.996
If you know something
that can help us prove...

408
00:19:46.079 --> 00:19:49.040
I don't. Now please. let me go.

409
00:19:56.923 --> 00:19:59.134
She couldn't even look us in the eye.

410
00:19:59.217 --> 00:20:02.220
Could be a guilty conscience.
Let's play it out.

411
00:20:02.303 --> 00:20:04.597
She's a strung-out teen back in the day.

412
00:20:04.681 --> 00:20:07.642
Got mixed up in the ketamine buy.
The agent's death.

413
00:20:07.726 --> 00:20:08.852
Her dad takes the fall for her.

414
00:20:08.935 --> 00:20:11.438
When he's looking at his last meal.
she finally caves.

415
00:20:11.521 --> 00:20:12.397
Writes a letter to save his life.

416
00:20:12.480 --> 00:20:14.816
I'll see if she has a rap sheet.
prior drug convictions.

417
00:20:14.899 --> 00:20:18.361
Okay. I have to meet Agent Rennett
about the First Lady's case.

418
00:20:18.445 --> 00:20:19.571
See you in the White House in an hour?

419
00:20:19.654 --> 00:20:22.323
- I'll call as soon as I hear something.
- Okay.

420
00:20:23.324 --> 00:20:24.492
Hey.

421
00:20:24.576 --> 00:20:27.704
- You've been scarce.
- Yeah. it's three-letter day.

422
00:20:27.787 --> 00:20:29.956
Is that some sort of postal holiday?

423
00:20:30.040 --> 00:20:32.751
No. it's... What do we have on the banker?

424
00:20:33.418 --> 00:20:35.503
Our Mr. Lang has dual citizenship.

425
00:20:35.587 --> 00:20:38.256
St. Lucia and the UK.
Multiple passports.

426
00:20:38.339 --> 00:20:40.425
He landed here
using his St. Lucia passport.

427
00:20:40.508 --> 00:20:43.094
Used his British one to pass into Canada
a few days ago.

428
00:20:43.178 --> 00:20:45.889
He's exploiting multiple identities
so we can't catch him in real time.

429
00:20:45.972 --> 00:20:48.224
Good way to stay one step
ahead of the banking regulators.

430
00:20:48.308 --> 00:20:50.810
By the time our systems update.
he could be in Kathmandu.

431
00:20:50.894 --> 00:20:52.062
We have to find him.

432
00:20:52.145 --> 00:20:54.898
He's the First Lady's last hope
to avoid the FBI inquiry.

433
00:20:54.981 --> 00:20:56.066
Yeah.

434
00:20:56.149 --> 00:20:58.401
Alfonso Lang has a condo in Georgetown

435
00:20:58.485 --> 00:21:02.322
he leases through a closely held
corporation called Montserrat Alliance.

436
00:21:02.405 --> 00:21:03.698
I'm texting you the address.

437
00:21:03.782 --> 00:21:05.158
We don't know that he's in the country.

438
00:21:05.241 --> 00:21:08.870
I do. I can trace a purchase to
a company credit card 90 minutes ago.

439
00:21:08.953 --> 00:21:11.873
- <i>A massage parlor in Dupont.</i>
- Thanks. Chuck.

440
00:21:11.956 --> 00:21:14.751
Lang's local.
Chuck is texting us the deets.

441
00:21:14.834 --> 00:21:17.796
If we can get Lang to confess
that he was working at Lloyd's behest

442
00:21:17.879 --> 00:21:20.548
to make it look like the First Lady
was getting a payola from Icarus.

443
00:21:20.632 --> 00:21:21.800
we can clear her name.

444
00:21:21.883 --> 00:21:24.594
Great. I'm gonna hit the loo.
I'll see you in a second.

445
00:21:49.404 --> 00:21:50.905
You got a partial plate?

446
00:21:50.989 --> 00:21:52.323
First three letters.
Chuck's running it.

447
00:21:53.158 --> 00:21:55.827
- There's a lesson here.
- What's that?

448
00:21:55.910 --> 00:21:57.871
You shouldn't beat up bankers without me.

449
00:21:57.954 --> 00:22:00.498
Especially bankers
who want to frame the First Lady.

450
00:22:00.582 --> 00:22:03.168
You think you could've
gotten out of the way of that car?

451
00:22:03.251 --> 00:22:06.171
Nope. I would've shot the guy
before he got in it.

452
00:22:08.631 --> 00:22:11.384
Mr. Lang? Hannah Wells. FBI.

453
00:22:13.803 --> 00:22:15.180
TV's on.

454
00:22:16.139 --> 00:22:17.807
You sure that's not someone
calling for help?

455
00:22:17.891 --> 00:22:20.268
Exigent circumstances.
No need for a warrant.

456
00:22:20.351 --> 00:22:21.728
You really have been here too long.

457
00:22:23.313 --> 00:22:24.731
I've been here longer.

458
00:22:29.903 --> 00:22:31.029
Hello?

459
00:22:32.447 --> 00:22:33.406
Mr. Lang?

460
00:22:40.163 --> 00:22:41.831
We just missed him.

461
00:22:43.666 --> 00:22:45.043
Someone tipped him off.

462
00:22:46.002 --> 00:22:48.504
Colonel Baines.
we have more questions about Kandahar.

463
00:22:48.588 --> 00:22:50.506
Those are the GPS coordinates
of Sergeant Goff's phone

464
00:22:50.590 --> 00:22:52.508
during the battle in which he was killed.

465
00:22:52.592 --> 00:22:54.677
You know what's interesting
about these coordinates?

466
00:22:54.761 --> 00:22:57.013
They put Sergeant Goff
in the middle of the battle.

467
00:22:57.096 --> 00:22:58.389
not a click away doing recon.

468
00:22:58.473 --> 00:23:00.516
That's the information I had.

469
00:23:00.600 --> 00:23:02.268
Let me show you the information we have.

470
00:23:02.352 --> 00:23:05.897
This is a divorce filing.
Your divorce filing.

471
00:23:05.980 --> 00:23:08.483
And it lists adultery as the grounds.

472
00:23:08.566 --> 00:23:10.526
An affair your wife had
with Sergeant Goff.

473
00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:14.113
Filing a false report
is a court-martial offense.

474
00:23:14.197 --> 00:23:17.075
Dishonorable discharge. Prison time.
I don't need to tell you that.

475
00:23:17.158 --> 00:23:18.701
No. you don't.

476
00:23:18.785 --> 00:23:21.079
So you will amend your statement
of Sergeant Goff's conduct.

477
00:23:21.162 --> 00:23:24.499
And you'll recommend that he be
posthumously awarded the Medal of Honor.

478
00:23:27.752 --> 00:23:28.920
Okay.

479
00:23:30.713 --> 00:23:31.714
I'll do that.

480
00:23:32.632 --> 00:23:33.466
Thank you.

481
00:23:33.549 --> 00:23:35.635
And I won't leave out any of it.

482
00:23:35.718 --> 00:23:37.887
Not how he betrayed my trust.

483
00:23:37.971 --> 00:23:41.391
Or seduced my wife.
Or ruined my marriage. or any of it.

484
00:23:42.308 --> 00:23:45.436
And his widow can frame my statement
right next to his Medal of Honor.

485
00:23:51.067 --> 00:23:53.319
So both of you disagree
with regards to Sergeant Goff?

486
00:23:54.279 --> 00:23:57.615
Yes. We both agree
he should be recognized for his valor.

487
00:23:57.699 --> 00:24:01.244
But medals are for the living.
not the dead. They provide comfort.

488
00:24:01.327 --> 00:24:03.329
If we award this medal to Sergeant Goff.

489
00:24:03.413 --> 00:24:05.665
his wife will also learn
about his infidelity.

490
00:24:05.748 --> 00:24:07.333
And I disagree.

491
00:24:07.417 --> 00:24:10.628
These inquiries have a narrow focus.
to determine the facts on the battlefield.

492
00:24:10.712 --> 00:24:12.547
Which deserve commendation.

493
00:24:12.630 --> 00:24:15.800
Yes. Once you factor extraneous
personal circumstances into the mix...

494
00:24:15.883 --> 00:24:18.970
The medal is about
extraneous personal circumstances.

495
00:24:19.053 --> 00:24:20.346
What it will mean to the next of kin.

496
00:24:20.430 --> 00:24:23.308
The greatest gift
we can give the next of kin is the truth.

497
00:24:26.060 --> 00:24:30.356
I would like to meet with Mrs. Goff
and her son. here in the Oval Office.

498
00:24:30.982 --> 00:24:32.025
Absolutely.

499
00:24:33.067 --> 00:24:34.986
May I address another matter?

500
00:24:36.195 --> 00:24:37.322
Sure. what is it?

501
00:24:37.947 --> 00:24:40.158
I'm here championing for transparency.

502
00:24:40.241 --> 00:24:42.827
I'm ashamed to admit
I haven't been as transparent with you

503
00:24:42.910 --> 00:24:45.747
as I should have been
regarding a personnel issue.

504
00:24:46.914 --> 00:24:48.249
I'm listening.

505
00:24:50.084 --> 00:24:53.338
A few days ago.
Seth was arrested and charged...

506
00:24:53.421 --> 00:24:54.672
I already know about it.

507
00:24:56.841 --> 00:24:57.759
You do?

508
00:24:57.842 --> 00:25:01.012
The District of Columbia DA is a friend.
We play cards together.

509
00:25:01.095 --> 00:25:03.264
He told me as soon as I got back
from Kabul.

510
00:25:04.599 --> 00:25:06.976
I'm sorry
we didn't have this conversation sooner.

511
00:25:07.060 --> 00:25:08.394
So am I.

512
00:25:09.228 --> 00:25:11.230
The point is. we're having it now.

513
00:25:11.939 --> 00:25:13.858
I know that the White House
is like a family.

514
00:25:13.941 --> 00:25:16.527
I can't imagine
how difficult it is for you sometimes

515
00:25:16.611 --> 00:25:17.779
in the trenches with everyone.

516
00:25:17.862 --> 00:25:18.738
Yes. sir.

517
00:25:18.821 --> 00:25:20.281
But you work for me

518
00:25:20.365 --> 00:25:23.159
and I can't do my job
when I'm kept in the dark.

519
00:25:24.077 --> 00:25:27.747
I rely on you to counsel me
through these kinds of matters.

520
00:25:28.664 --> 00:25:29.665
Understood.

521
00:25:30.375 --> 00:25:32.085
Having said that...

522
00:25:37.507 --> 00:25:39.342
What do you think I should do about Seth?

523
00:25:50.937 --> 00:25:54.107
Look at them.
So innocent. So vulnerable.

524
00:25:54.190 --> 00:25:55.650
They're bees. Lyor.

525
00:25:56.567 --> 00:25:57.944
Wait. Lyor. hold on.

526
00:25:58.027 --> 00:26:01.322
<i>J'accuse.</i> Helen Adamson.
Justice must be done.

527
00:26:01.406 --> 00:26:03.699
Wait. wait. Lyor. relax.

528
00:26:03.783 --> 00:26:04.951
I am relaxed.

529
00:26:05.576 --> 00:26:08.955
Relaxed as someone about to confront
a woman over apicide can be.

530
00:26:09.956 --> 00:26:11.249
- That's not a word.
- Yes. it is.

531
00:26:11.332 --> 00:26:13.418
- We don't know that she killed the bees.
- Yes. we do.

532
00:26:13.501 --> 00:26:15.837
- You have to stop ringing the bell.
- No. I don't.

533
00:26:17.755 --> 00:26:19.924
Sorry. Just got out of the shower.

534
00:26:20.007 --> 00:26:21.467
We need to talk.

535
00:26:21.551 --> 00:26:24.846
- Oh. okay. Eddie stepped out.
- Oh. just the three of us. then.

536
00:26:24.929 --> 00:26:27.181
We can come back
at a more convenient time. Thanks.

537
00:26:27.265 --> 00:26:29.225
I'll just be a minute. Come in.

538
00:26:29.308 --> 00:26:31.394
Great.

539
00:26:32.270 --> 00:26:35.314
Make yourselves comfortable
and I'll be right back.

540
00:26:35.398 --> 00:26:37.358
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

541
00:26:42.155 --> 00:26:43.448
What are you doing?

542
00:26:44.031 --> 00:26:45.032
Hey.

543
00:26:46.868 --> 00:26:48.411
You realize this gives me more evidence

544
00:26:48.494 --> 00:26:50.079
for your
involuntary commitment application?

545
00:26:50.163 --> 00:26:52.665
She killed the bees. Thousands of them.

546
00:26:52.748 --> 00:26:54.959
- She didn't. The FAA did.
- Wrong.

547
00:26:55.042 --> 00:26:57.587
Two of the three colonies
collapsed completely.

548
00:26:57.670 --> 00:26:59.213
The third seems to be fine.

549
00:26:59.297 --> 00:27:01.257
Which means that while the radar
may have weakened them.

550
00:27:01.340 --> 00:27:03.634
she applied the coup de grâce.

551
00:27:07.138 --> 00:27:08.306
And this was it.

552
00:27:12.268 --> 00:27:15.188
Helen Adamson
is the colony collapse disorder.

553
00:27:15.271 --> 00:27:18.232
Okay. Animal Planet.
Slow down and take me through it.

554
00:27:18.316 --> 00:27:20.485
This is royal jelly. A massive amount.

555
00:27:20.568 --> 00:27:22.320
You take too much from the hive.
the queen stops laying.

556
00:27:22.403 --> 00:27:23.529
The larvae starts dying.

557
00:27:23.613 --> 00:27:25.948
- Why would she kill the bees?
- Jealousy.

558
00:27:26.073 --> 00:27:28.868
Have you seen the house?
It's a glorious shrine to bees.

559
00:27:28.951 --> 00:27:30.912
She gets rid of the bees.
she gets her husband back?

560
00:27:30.995 --> 00:27:34.332
Yes. Except. he's going to leave
when he learns she's a serial killer.

561
00:27:34.415 --> 00:27:35.875
He's not learning anything.

562
00:27:35.958 --> 00:27:37.793
Our remit is to save the bees.
not wreck their marriage.

563
00:27:37.877 --> 00:27:39.670
We'll save the bees
by wrecking the marriage.

564
00:27:39.754 --> 00:27:42.089
No. no. Listen. I have a plan. okay?

565
00:27:42.173 --> 00:27:43.633
It'll save your bees.

566
00:27:43.716 --> 00:27:46.302
and the federal government
from an alienation of affection lawsuit.

567
00:27:46.385 --> 00:27:49.096
Now. sit down. shut up and let me explain.

568
00:27:52.475 --> 00:27:54.894
Why do they call it the Oval Office?

569
00:27:54.977 --> 00:27:56.938
Because it's shaped like an oval.

570
00:27:57.563 --> 00:27:58.397
What's an oval?

571
00:27:59.148 --> 00:28:01.317
Sort of like a circle. but squished.

572
00:28:03.319 --> 00:28:04.987
Is there a triangle office?

573
00:28:05.071 --> 00:28:08.032
- Danny. that's enough questions.
- No. it's fine.

574
00:28:08.115 --> 00:28:11.369
There isn't.
but it would be really cool if there was.

575
00:28:11.452 --> 00:28:12.995
Why don't we have a seat?

576
00:28:15.957 --> 00:28:19.544
Mrs. Goff. I am very sorry.

577
00:28:19.627 --> 00:28:23.339
but I am not gonna be able
to present your husband with the medal.

578
00:28:23.923 --> 00:28:26.008
Our investigation was inconclusive.

579
00:28:26.634 --> 00:28:28.261
Memories fade. Witnesses disappear.

580
00:28:28.344 --> 00:28:32.139
There's a high standard of proof
for this sort of thing.

581
00:28:33.766 --> 00:28:34.851
I understand. sir.

582
00:28:35.434 --> 00:28:37.061
I asked you both here today

583
00:28:37.144 --> 00:28:40.398
because I wanted to present you with this.
from me.

584
00:28:43.442 --> 00:28:45.570
And I wanted to talk to you. Danny.

585
00:28:46.863 --> 00:28:48.114
About your father.

586
00:28:50.575 --> 00:28:51.409
Okay.

587
00:28:52.243 --> 00:28:54.287
I want you to know how brave he was.

588
00:28:56.038 --> 00:28:59.208
There are people alive today
because of what your father did.

589
00:28:59.292 --> 00:29:00.585
That's what made him a hero.

590
00:29:03.212 --> 00:29:04.589
My dad was brave.

591
00:29:06.716 --> 00:29:09.176
Yes. he was. Very.

592
00:29:10.136 --> 00:29:12.555
And if anyone asks you how you know that.

593
00:29:13.681 --> 00:29:16.559
tell them that the president
of the United States told you.

594
00:29:22.023 --> 00:29:23.190
Thank you.

595
00:29:24.567 --> 00:29:27.236
No. Thank you.

596
00:29:29.614 --> 00:29:33.284
We are pleased to report that the FAA
has agreed to redirect its radio waves

597
00:29:33.367 --> 00:29:35.828
so that your colonies
are no longer affected.

598
00:29:35.912 --> 00:29:37.163
- Really?
- Yes.

599
00:29:37.246 --> 00:29:39.832
So we anticipate
a resurgence in your bee population.

600
00:29:39.916 --> 00:29:41.959
A robust resurgence.

601
00:29:42.043 --> 00:29:44.795
See. Helen.
I told you President Kirkman cared.

602
00:29:44.879 --> 00:29:47.340
The person you should be thanking
is your wife.

603
00:29:47.423 --> 00:29:49.634
She's the one who brought the FAA to heel.

604
00:29:50.134 --> 00:29:53.054
- I don't know what to say.
- We'll let you say it in private.

605
00:29:53.137 --> 00:29:54.221
No. wait.

606
00:29:56.724 --> 00:29:59.936
I'm ashamed of my behavior.

607
00:30:00.019 --> 00:30:02.521
I've repaid my wife's devotion
with treachery.

608
00:30:02.605 --> 00:30:05.274
I wanna confess it
in front of everyone here.

609
00:30:05.358 --> 00:30:06.776
- Eddie?
- We should go. Lyor.

610
00:30:07.777 --> 00:30:11.280
- Your roses? The ones the deer ate?
- What about them?

611
00:30:11.364 --> 00:30:15.534
- It wasn't the deer. I poisoned them.
- What?

612
00:30:15.618 --> 00:30:17.119
- Now. Lyor.
- You're being rude.

613
00:30:17.203 --> 00:30:18.829
He wants to unburden himself.

614
00:30:18.913 --> 00:30:22.291
They were drawing them away
from better food sources.

615
00:30:22.375 --> 00:30:24.543
I was desperate.
Oh. God. I am so sorry.

616
00:30:24.627 --> 00:30:27.838
I am sorry. too. That I didn't kill more
of those parasites.

617
00:30:27.922 --> 00:30:30.591
- You killed my bees?
- Not enough of them. you bastard.

618
00:30:30.675 --> 00:30:31.801
- You murderer!
- You're the murderer!

619
00:30:31.884 --> 00:30:33.511
- Now we can go.
- My mother was right about you!

620
00:30:33.594 --> 00:30:34.929
Oh. speaking of someone
I wanna kill.

621
00:30:35.012 --> 00:30:36.430
Don't you dare mention her name.

622
00:30:36.514 --> 00:30:38.933
I should have
married Lance Burtleson.

623
00:30:39.016 --> 00:30:40.309
Lance? Please!

624
00:30:43.064 --> 00:30:44.983
Someone tried to run you down?

625
00:30:45.066 --> 00:30:47.193
It's an occupational hazard.
I'm fine. Talk to me.

626
00:30:47.277 --> 00:30:48.862
<i>I checked Tracy in the system.</i>

627
00:30:48.945 --> 00:30:51.156
No record.
But I got a hit from another Dern.

628
00:30:51.239 --> 00:30:52.949
- Her brother. Frank.
- <i>What's his collar for?</i>

629
00:30:53.033 --> 00:30:54.826
Drug conviction in 2001.

630
00:30:54.909 --> 00:30:57.203
Six months after his dad's conviction.

631
00:30:57.287 --> 00:30:59.914
Misdemeanor and possession of ketamine.

632
00:30:59.998 --> 00:31:02.042
Which was a rare designer drug
back in 2001.

633
00:31:02.125 --> 00:31:04.252
Meaning if Chandler Dern
was covering for someone.

634
00:31:04.336 --> 00:31:05.712
it wasn't his daughter.

635
00:31:06.254 --> 00:31:08.590
- <i>Keep each other posted.</i>
- Deal.

636
00:31:09.466 --> 00:31:11.468
Is the president going to pardon me?

637
00:31:11.551 --> 00:31:12.886
Not unless you tell the truth.

638
00:31:12.969 --> 00:31:16.014
I've been telling the truth for 16 years.
I'm innocent.

639
00:31:16.097 --> 00:31:17.432
I believe you.

640
00:31:18.308 --> 00:31:20.727
And I also believe you know who's not.

641
00:31:20.810 --> 00:31:23.271
This is Frank's arrest record.

642
00:31:24.898 --> 00:31:26.066
What does that have to do with anything?

643
00:31:26.149 --> 00:31:28.193
We both know what happened that night.

644
00:31:28.276 --> 00:31:32.364
Your son tried to buy ketamine.
It went wrong. He killed Carl Marley.

645
00:31:32.447 --> 00:31:33.573
That's a lie.

646
00:31:33.657 --> 00:31:36.868
You took the fall.
And made your daughter keep the secret.

647
00:31:36.951 --> 00:31:38.662
And it destroyed her.

648
00:31:38.745 --> 00:31:40.664
But she kept faith with you.

649
00:31:41.915 --> 00:31:45.335
Until she couldn't anymore because
she didn't wanna watch her father die.

650
00:31:45.418 --> 00:31:49.005
If you think I'm gonna give up my son.
you must not have children.

651
00:31:49.089 --> 00:31:51.424
You've been tried and convicted
for this crime.

652
00:31:51.508 --> 00:31:54.302
No prosecutor on Earth
will try to charge Frank for this now.

653
00:31:54.386 --> 00:31:56.304
let alone try to convince a jury
to convict him.

654
00:31:56.388 --> 00:31:57.847
But the world will know.

655
00:31:57.931 --> 00:32:01.559
Mr. Dern. if you want
the president to pardon you.

656
00:32:01.643 --> 00:32:04.729
he needs to hear the truth from your lips.

657
00:32:07.649 --> 00:32:10.819
I regret the damage done to Tracy
more than anything.

658
00:32:11.444 --> 00:32:15.198
And I would gladly die
if it would make her whole again.

659
00:32:15.281 --> 00:32:16.825
But I can't help her now.

660
00:32:18.493 --> 00:32:20.995
I can help Frank.

661
00:32:21.079 --> 00:32:25.166
He has a life. And I will sacrifice mine
so that he can keep his.

662
00:32:25.250 --> 00:32:26.543
Guard!

663
00:32:33.091 --> 00:32:34.634
- Hey.
- Hey...

664
00:32:34.718 --> 00:32:36.094
This will just take a second.

665
00:32:36.177 --> 00:32:39.013
I've decided to offer the president
my resignation.

666
00:32:39.097 --> 00:32:40.348
What?

667
00:32:40.432 --> 00:32:42.934
I've been skulking around here
the last two days.

668
00:32:43.017 --> 00:32:44.477
I know he knows I've been arrested.

669
00:32:44.561 --> 00:32:46.479
I can see it in the way he looks at me.

670
00:32:46.563 --> 00:32:49.190
I can hear it in his tone.
He put me on bee patrol.

671
00:32:49.274 --> 00:32:51.484
He cares about bees.

672
00:32:51.568 --> 00:32:52.944
Bee patrol with Lyor.

673
00:32:53.027 --> 00:32:55.447
Yeah.

674
00:32:55.530 --> 00:32:58.324
I'm in the doghouse.
I don't know how to get out.

675
00:32:58.408 --> 00:33:00.452
So I figure I'll offer him my resignation.

676
00:33:00.535 --> 00:33:02.412
If he accepts. I know I'm good.
If not...

677
00:33:02.495 --> 00:33:04.497
- He won't accept it.
- How do you know that?

678
00:33:08.626 --> 00:33:12.756
Because I told him to fire you.
And he declined.

679
00:33:15.049 --> 00:33:17.218
- I had to be objective.
- No. I know.

680
00:33:17.302 --> 00:33:20.805
An objective Emily would view
your behavior as disloyal.

681
00:33:20.889 --> 00:33:24.559
You compromised the one person
you can't compromise.

682
00:33:24.642 --> 00:33:27.395
- And you did it willingly.
- I know.

683
00:33:29.314 --> 00:33:31.107
And you compromised me.

684
00:33:32.692 --> 00:33:38.406
And I've looked at this
every which way since it's gone down.

685
00:33:39.532 --> 00:33:41.409
I've reconsidered every option.

686
00:33:42.577 --> 00:33:44.245
And here's where I come out.

687
00:33:46.247 --> 00:33:47.540
I would do it again.

688
00:33:48.583 --> 00:33:51.836
Because Michael's my brother
and I protect my family.

689
00:33:51.920 --> 00:33:53.171
I know.

690
00:33:53.922 --> 00:33:56.341
And that's exactly why he won't fire you.

691
00:33:57.300 --> 00:34:01.012
You get one "get out of jail free" card
and you just used it.

692
00:34:02.639 --> 00:34:04.182
So what now?

693
00:34:05.683 --> 00:34:06.851
Come here.

694
00:34:15.568 --> 00:34:18.404
Now go forth and sin no more.

695
00:34:18.488 --> 00:34:19.489
Thanks.

696
00:34:20.406 --> 00:34:22.450
For what? Trying to get you fired?

697
00:34:23.284 --> 00:34:24.702
For always doing the right thing.

698
00:34:30.708 --> 00:34:33.002
The right thing to do.

699
00:34:36.089 --> 00:34:38.925
Sometimes it seems impossible
to know what that is anymore.

700
00:34:39.008 --> 00:34:40.176
Yes. sir.

701
00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:44.889
Your case summary makes it perfectly clear
that Mr. Dern covered for his son.

702
00:34:46.391 --> 00:34:48.893
In his mind. trying to protect his family.

703
00:34:49.477 --> 00:34:54.190
However misguided. I don't think
anyone deserves to die for that.

704
00:34:54.274 --> 00:34:55.483
I agree. sir.

705
00:34:56.526 --> 00:34:58.820
But the fact remains
there's a dead federal agent

706
00:34:58.903 --> 00:35:00.446
whose murderer's walking the streets

707
00:35:00.530 --> 00:35:03.157
because Mr. Dern chose
to obstruct justice.

708
00:35:03.241 --> 00:35:05.118
And he has to pay for that.

709
00:35:09.205 --> 00:35:10.707
But not with his life.

710
00:35:11.291 --> 00:35:12.542
So you're commuting his sentence.

711
00:35:12.625 --> 00:35:14.085
Yes. but not his conviction.

712
00:35:14.168 --> 00:35:17.672
He'll spend his life in prison
unless he tells the truth.

713
00:35:19.340 --> 00:35:22.802
Can you patch me through
to the penitentiary? Thanks.

714
00:35:24.331 --> 00:35:26.125
The car that nearly hit you
was a silver sedan.

715
00:35:26.208 --> 00:35:28.710
Maryland plates that start with SK1.

716
00:35:28.794 --> 00:35:30.462
I narrowed it to 19 people.

717
00:35:30.546 --> 00:35:33.132
Did you cross-reference this list
for connections to Alfonso Lang?

718
00:35:33.215 --> 00:35:34.091
Yeah. Nothing.

719
00:35:34.174 --> 00:35:36.218
What about the Federal Bank of St. Lucia?

720
00:35:36.301 --> 00:35:37.761
Ran that search. too. <i>Nada.</i>

721
00:35:37.845 --> 00:35:38.846
I'll run a deeper search.

722
00:35:38.929 --> 00:35:42.599
Look for even tangential contacts between
these people and Icarus. Lloyd.

723
00:35:42.683 --> 00:35:44.518
Nineteen cars is a lot of cars.

724
00:35:44.601 --> 00:35:46.186
Yeah. It's a lot of cars.

725
00:35:46.812 --> 00:35:49.064
But the person who tried to kill me
would wanna make sure

726
00:35:49.148 --> 00:35:50.983
that this car wasn't traced back to them.

727
00:35:51.900 --> 00:35:54.027
You know what's interesting
about this list?

728
00:35:54.903 --> 00:35:57.489
One of the cars on it
was in an accident three days ago.

729
00:36:02.077 --> 00:36:03.829
- Where are you going?
- I got a hunch.

730
00:36:03.912 --> 00:36:06.165
If I'm right.
I'll know who tried to kill me.

731
00:36:10.794 --> 00:36:13.213
That's good work. boys.
See you tomorrow.

732
00:36:15.799 --> 00:36:17.092
Agent Wells.

733
00:36:17.176 --> 00:36:19.136
I assume you heard
about your father's commutation.

734
00:36:19.219 --> 00:36:21.472
I did. Thank you for all your work.

735
00:36:21.555 --> 00:36:24.057
- It's been a great relief.
- I'm sure it is.

736
00:36:24.141 --> 00:36:27.811
It would be terrible to watch him die
for a murder you committed.

737
00:36:30.272 --> 00:36:33.484
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Drop the act.

738
00:36:33.567 --> 00:36:35.402
We both know
you're never going to answer for it.

739
00:36:35.486 --> 00:36:36.778
But you will answer for something.

740
00:36:36.862 --> 00:36:38.906
- You're making a big mistake.
- No. you did.

741
00:36:38.989 --> 00:36:42.784
When you used a car that your shop
was repairing to try and kill me.

742
00:36:43.327 --> 00:36:47.039
We know you were driving the car.
Your office manager saw you get into it.

743
00:36:47.122 --> 00:36:48.707
- She's mistaken.
- Put your hands up.

744
00:36:48.790 --> 00:36:50.000
On the car. Now!

745
00:36:51.084 --> 00:36:53.629
Saving your dad meant
that I would ruin your reputation.

746
00:36:53.712 --> 00:36:55.130
so you tried to run me down.
Guess what?

747
00:36:55.214 --> 00:36:58.884
It's been 16 years. but you're finally
going to jail. you son of a bitch.

748
00:37:08.101 --> 00:37:10.062
I have the First Lady for you.

749
00:37:10.145 --> 00:37:13.732
Thank you. Ava. Hey.
I was just heading up to the Residence.

750
00:37:13.815 --> 00:37:17.110
This couldn't wait.
You need to fire John Foerstel.

751
00:37:17.194 --> 00:37:19.404
- Why?
- Because he is using his office

752
00:37:19.488 --> 00:37:20.906
to create headlines for himself.

753
00:37:20.989 --> 00:37:24.159
He's purposely muddying the waters
for potential political gain.

754
00:37:24.243 --> 00:37:26.578
He's betraying his oath of office.
that is why.

755
00:37:26.662 --> 00:37:29.331
- Alex. it's not that easy.
- Yes. it is.

756
00:37:29.414 --> 00:37:31.291
Patrick Lloyd has been dead
for two months.

757
00:37:31.375 --> 00:37:33.252
We are still being haunted by him.

758
00:37:33.335 --> 00:37:34.836
The fabricated bank account.

759
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:38.298
The conspiracy with Icarus
that doesn't even exist.

760
00:37:38.382 --> 00:37:40.676
- None of this is real.
- I know.

761
00:37:40.759 --> 00:37:43.428
Why are you letting us get dragged down
by an investigation

762
00:37:43.512 --> 00:37:45.013
when you can do something about it?

763
00:37:45.097 --> 00:37:48.058
My staff wants me
to appoint a special prosecutor.

764
00:37:48.141 --> 00:37:49.977
You want me to fire Foerstel.

765
00:37:50.060 --> 00:37:52.062
- You're all missing the point.
- What is the point?

766
00:37:52.145 --> 00:37:54.856
Your mother committed a federal crime.

767
00:37:54.940 --> 00:37:56.066
Thirty years ago. maybe.

768
00:37:56.149 --> 00:37:57.985
but she committed a crime.
There are consequences.

769
00:37:58.068 --> 00:38:00.404
I can't just change the rules
because it suits us.

770
00:38:00.487 --> 00:38:03.407
John Foerstel is preparing
to run for Senate.

771
00:38:03.490 --> 00:38:05.325
He is not playing by the rules.

772
00:38:05.409 --> 00:38:06.660
Yes. he is. damn it!

773
00:38:06.743 --> 00:38:09.329
He's doing his job.
maybe not the way we want him to.

774
00:38:10.122 --> 00:38:13.292
I can't fire him for that.
If I did. who would I be?

775
00:38:14.585 --> 00:38:16.169
My husband.

776
00:38:21.216 --> 00:38:22.384
Wow.

777
00:38:23.885 --> 00:38:25.971
I can't believe you just said that.

778
00:38:27.931 --> 00:38:29.641
You're questioning
my commitment as a husband

779
00:38:29.725 --> 00:38:31.435
because I won't interfere
in an investigation

780
00:38:31.518 --> 00:38:33.979
where we've done absolutely nothing wrong?

781
00:38:34.605 --> 00:38:38.609
You're a hell of a lawyer. Alex.
but you're a lousy defendant.

782
00:38:56.293 --> 00:38:58.545
- More wine?
- Sure.

783
00:39:00.714 --> 00:39:01.715
Uh-oh.

784
00:39:01.798 --> 00:39:03.967
- Are we out?
- Yep.

785
00:39:14.728 --> 00:39:16.438
Burning the midnight oil. Chuck?

786
00:39:16.521 --> 00:39:19.775
Yes. listen. I got something.
I ran Lang's cell phone.

787
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:22.736
You were right. Somebody called him
right before you got to his condo.

788
00:39:22.819 --> 00:39:24.655
- From a burner.
- Do we know who it was?

789
00:39:24.738 --> 00:39:28.533
No. But I triangulated the signal
based on the cell phone towers.

790
00:39:29.785 --> 00:39:32.663
Call came from 4th and H. 2:22 p.m.

791
00:39:35.582 --> 00:39:38.001
I'm gonna hit the loo.
I'll meet you there.

792
00:39:38.085 --> 00:39:40.087
Hannah. Are you there?

793
00:39:40.712 --> 00:39:44.091
Yeah. Thanks. Chuck.
I'll talk to you soon.

794
00:39:46.551 --> 00:39:49.137
Hey. what's it gonna be?
Work or pleasure?

795
00:39:53.975 --> 00:39:55.310
Pleasure.

796
00:40:07.939 --> 00:40:12.939
Subtitles by explosiveskull
